[Shell]

Running from shell you can use the following arguments:

  rVNCd [options]

Options:

  -v0 .. -v3 or --verbose
    Controls verbosity level.
      -v0  Output off (except errors)
      -v1  Normal output
      -v2  Extra output
      -v3  Debug output

    NOTE:
    When set from Shell, verbose level is locked and cannot be changed
    by the config file (but GUI may still change it).

  -p or --port <port>
    Set the TCP port to listen on.
    Overrides config file setting.

  -c or --config <file>
    Select which config file to use.

  -h or --help
    Print shell options and exit.

  --noarexx
    Don't add ARexx port on startup.

  --nocxbroker
    Don't add Commodities Broker on startup.

Default config file:
  rVNCd.Config


------------------------------------------------------------

[ARexx]

ARexx port name: RVNCD

Commands:

  STARTSERVER
    Starts the server if not already running.
    Safe to call multiple times.
    Result value indicates success.


  STOPSERVER
    Stops the server if running.
    Safe to call if already stopped.


  RESTARTSERVER
    Stops the server (if running) and starts it again.
    If not running, it will simply start.
    Result value indicates success.


  SERVERSTATUS
    Returns whether the server is running or not.


  QUIT
    Stops the server (if running) and exits the program.


  LOADCONFIG - "FILE/F"

  SAVECONFIG

  SAVEASCONFIG - "FILE/F"

  SAVEDEFAULTCONFIG

  HELP

  FORCEQUIT

------------------------------------------------------------

[CONFIG]

The config file is divided into sections using [SectionName].

------------------------------------------------------------

[Program]

  Verbose - (U8) 0-3
    Default verbosity level when not set from Shell.

    Values:
      0 = Off (errors only)
      1 = Normal
      2 = Extra
      3 = Debug

    Default:
      0


  DisableGUI - (U8) 0-1
    Don't open GUI libraries on startup to keep resource usage low.

    Values:
      0 = Alloc/Open gui
      1 = Don't get gui resources

    Default:
      0


  DisableARexx - (U8) 0-1
    Don't start ARexx.

    Values:
      0 = Startup ARexx
      1 = Don't run ARexx client

    Default:
      0


  DisableCxBroker - (U8) 0-1
    Don't start CxBroker.

    Values:
      0 = Startup CxBroker
      1 = Don't run CxBroker client

    Default:
      0

------------------------------------------------------------

[Server]

  Name (STR)
    Server name exchanged during VNC handshake.

    Default:
      Amiga VNC Server


  Port - (U32) 0-65535
    TCP port to listen on.
    Can be overridden by Shell option.

    Default:
      5900


  DelayFrequency (S32) 0-500
    Number of tiles processed before inserting a short pause.
    Set to 0 for maximum speed.

    Default:
      150


  DisableBlanker (U8) 0-1
    Prevents screen blanker while a client is connected.
    Blanker is restored on disconnect.

    Default:
      1 (True)


  SendClipboard (U8) 0-1
    Send Amiga clipboard text to client.
    Text only.

    Default:
      1 (True)


  ReadClipboard (U8) 0-1
    Update Amiga clipboard from client clipboard.
    Text only.

    Default:
      1 (True)


  AutoStart (U8) 0-1
    Automatically start server when program launches.

    Default:
      1 (True)


  ScanMethod (U8) 0-1
    Tile scanning order:
      0 = Linear
      1 = Random

    Default:
      0


  Password (STR)
    Enables VNC authentication (DES-based).
    Security is weak by protocol design.

    Default:
      Not set (Disabled)


  EncRRE (U8) 0-1
    Enable RRE encoding.
    Efficient for areas with large regions of identical color
    (e.g. Shell windows or solid Workbench backdrops).

    Default:
      1 (Enabled)


  EncZLIB (U8) 0-1
    Enable ZLIB compressed encoding.

    Default:
      1 (Enabled)


  SendBell (U8) 0-1
    Forward Intuition DisplayBeep() events to the VNC client
    as Bell messages.

    Default:
      1 (Enabled)


  TileSize (S32) 16-256
    Size of a single graphics tile in pixels.
    Smaller tiles may improve update granularity,
    larger tiles may reduce protocol overhead.

    Default:
      64


  Protocol33 (U8) 0-1
    Allow VNC protocol version 3.3.

    Default:
      1 (Enabled)


  Protocol37 (U8) 0-1
    Allow VNC protocol version 3.7.

    Default:
      1 (Enabled)


  PointerFile (STR)
    Filename of custom mouse pointer image.
    Used when PointerType is set to File.
    Maximum size: 64x64 pixels.

    Default:
      Not set


  PointerType (U8) 0-1
    Mouse pointer source:
      0 = System pointer
      1 = Custom pointer from PointerFile

    Default:
      0


  SendWatchDog (U32) 0-1000
    Interval (in milliseconds) for sending watchdog keep-alive
    packets to the client.
    0 disables watchdog messages.

    Default:
      0 (Disabled)


  EncRichCursor (U8) 0-1
    Enable RichCursor encoding.
    Sends cursor image to client so the client draws the pointer.

    Default:
      1 (Enabled)


  SendTileBuffer (U32) 0-1024
    Size of tile send buffer in kilobytes.
    Buffers outgoing tile data before sending.

    Default:
      64


------------------------------------------------------------

[Log]

  Enable (U8) 0-1
    Enable logging to disk.

    Default:
      1 (True)


  LogFile (STR)
    Base filename for log output.
    Extension ".txt" is added automatically.
    Files larger than 1MB are split (.002, .003, ...).

    Default:
      Logdata


  ProgramStart (U8) 0-1
    Log when program starts.

    Default:
      0 (False)


  ProgramStop (U8) 0-1
    Log when program exits.

    Default:
      0 (False)


  ServerStart (U8) 0-1
    Log when server starts.

    Default:
      1 (True)


  ServerStop (U8) 0-1
    Log when server stops.

    Default:
      1 (True)


  UserConnect (U8) 0-1
    Log when a client connects.

    Default:
      1 (True)


  Infos (U8) 0-1
    Log informational messages.

    Default:
      1 (True)


  Errors (U8) 0-1
    Log error messages.

    Default:
      1 (True)


  Warnings (U8) 0-1
    Log warning messages.

    Default:
      1 (True)


  UserDisconnect (U8) 0-1
    Log when a client disconnects.

    Default:
      1 (True)

------------------------------------------------------------

[IP]

NOTE:
WhiteList and BlackList were merged into a single list
for easier maintenance and better control.

  Allow
    IP addresses allowed to connect.
    Checked before Deny rules.
    Wildcards supported (e.g. 192.168.*.*).
    Unlimited entries.

    Default:
      none


  Block
    IP addresses blocked from connecting.
    Wildcards supported.
    Unlimited entries.

    Default:
      none

------------------------------------------------------------

[ACTIONS]

Allows execution of ARexx or Shell command strings on specific events.

  ProgramStopEnable (U8) 0-1
    Execute ProgramStopBuffer when program exits.

  ProgramStopBuffer (STR)
    Command executed on program shutdown.


  ProgramStartEnable (U8) 0-1
    Execute ProgramStartBuffer when program starts.

  ProgramStartBuffer (STR)
    Command executed on program startup.


  ServerStartEnable (U8) 0-1
    Execute ServerStartBuffer when server starts.

  ServerStartBuffer (STR)
    Command executed when VNC server starts listening.


  ServerStopEnable (U8) 0-1
    Execute ServerStopBuffer when server stops.

  ServerStopBuffer (STR)
    Command executed when VNC server shuts down.


  UserConnectEnable (U8) 0-1
    Execute UserConnectBuffer when a client connects.

  UserConnectBuffer (STR)
    Command executed on client connect.


  UserDisconnectEnable (U8) 0-1
    Execute UserDisconnectBuffer when a client disconnects.

  UserDisconnectBuffer (STR)
    Command executed on client disconnect.

